            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> with 30g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour </strong>in a large bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut the fillet[s] in half</p><p>Sprinkle both sides of the<strong> basa</strong> with <strong>flour</strong> until fully coated</p><p>Dip the<strong> floured basa</strong> into the <strong>batter</strong> and turn it several times until fully coated – this is your<strong> coated basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
